title: Sakhalin
author: Unknown
pages:
Sakhalin / Caxa.

This island is actually
part of the Russian
Federation. Sakhalin
was originally disputed
between Russia and
Japan up until World
War II when the
Soviets held it during
the final days of the
war. Japan no longer
lays claim to Sakhalin.
The largest city on

Sakhalin is
Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk
and is the
administrative centre
of Sakhalin Oblast. As
of 2010 the census
for the island is
497,973. It is notable
for having significant
natural resources.
